description: From Afrikaans, from Dutch mus (“a sparrow”).

entries.meaning: (South Africa) Any of various species of sparrow, especially Passer melanurus.
examples: Our four baby mossies have left the nest.

description: Diminutive formed from mosquito. Compare Dutch meuzie (“mosquito”).

entries.meaning: (UK, Australia, New Zealand, colloquial) A mosquito.
examples: She came out, standing a head taller than him, tugging a loose cotton shift into place, and made for a rough brick fireplace beside a pile of rusting pots and pans.
‘Come inside,’ Willi said. ‘The mossies will eat you alive out here.’
